caption: This place is fantastic. I’m sure there’s many good places to get pho in this city but this has been my favorite since i’ve lived here. It’s always amazing, and all the different options for customizing are excellent. And you can get extra containers if the broth—i swear that stuff cured me when i had the flu a couple years back. The non-pho menu items i’ve tried have all been excellent too, and i love the crunchy fresh spring rolls.
I love their vegan pho!

Lovely experience all around. I'm looking forward to going back. Parking is the only issue. Deliver if possible. 😉

I had the spicy lemongrass broth which was beyond amazing I love it more than the beef broth which is what I usually get. My friend got the vegetarian broth made from fuji apples and it was also really good with a hint of sweetness. We also got the seafood rolls. The rolls were two for $7 but they were a good size and cut into 3 pieces. Everything was fresh. Overall the environment, service and the food were great. Absolutely recommend, I come here whenever I want pho.

The vegan food here is incredible. I’ve had a few dishes and my favorites are the vegan vermicelli bowl (with tofu and sweet chili sauce) and the southern lemongrass soup with tofu (spices in this soup are out of this world and so is the tofu/fake meat). Everything is always super fresh and they are so kind. I feel fueled and energized after eating which is a huge win — highly recommend!

I love Pho and eat it at least once a week, if not more often.  While in DC I had an opportunity to visit Pho 14 for lunch.   Service was friendly and quick. Tables were packed in pretty tight (like most places in DC are) to make the most of the space so it feels a little cramped.  Spring rolls were a little gummy and peanut sauce was a bit bland.  Seafood Pho was outstanding though and I would definitely go back for this alone.  The broth was hearty and full of flavor and the shrimp was plentiful, plump, cleaned well and tasty.  I was so hungry I neglected to take any photos of my food but I definitely recommend Pho 14 for tasty pho - I would just skip the spring rolls on my next visit.

Absolutely delicious and super fresh food.  Summer rolls with fresh herbs and shrimp.  The fried egg rolla were great.  My husband enjoyed his Pho, which is totally customized.  I loved the bahn mi platter and my picky son had a delicious noodle bowl.

The pho, spring & egg rolls are staples and super yummy, but my favorite dish is definitely the papaya salad - haven’t found anything like it anywhere else and it’s so delicious. Definitely recommend trying this place out!

All in all this restaurant is very nice and great to try new food.

We started with a grilled chicken spring roll.  My husband doesn't like seafood, which is why we didn't order the traditional kind.  Unfortunately, the grilled meat spring rolls don't come with peanut sauce.  I then had beef bunh.  It was o.k.  I asked for both the housemade fish sauce and the sweet chili sauce (the sauces recommended on the menu).  A guy who was helping the waitress brought out some red chili sauce.  The waitress was angry with him because I guess it was the wrong sauce.  She kept saying that it was too spicy; that we wouldn't like it.  She did leave it on the table and went to get the sweet chili sauce.  I'm not sure what the waitress's definition of spicy is (or perhaps she thought that we were incapable of eating any amount of spice), but that "spicy" sauce was MILD.  I basically used the entire bowl myself and at no point during my meal, did the spiciness build.  The sweet chili sauce was far too sweet.  So in the end, I had a bowl of bunh that was too sweet and needed Sriracha to have any amount of spiciness.
